---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service">
  <div class="terms-container">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: December 29, 2025</p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>By accessing or using Strollcast, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the service.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Service Description</h2>
      <p>Strollcast transforms research papers into audio podcasts using AI-generated voices. The service is intended for educational and accessibility purposes.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. User Responsibilities</h2>
      <h3>You agree to:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Only submit papers that are publicly available or for which you have the right to create derivative works</li>
        <li>Not submit copyrighted content without appropriate permissions or licenses</li>
        <li>Not use the service for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Not attempt to circumvent any security measures</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Acceptable Content:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Papers published under open access licenses (CC-BY, CC-BY-SA, etc.)</li>
        <li>arXiv preprints (which grant a non-exclusive license for distribution)</li>
        <li>Your own original work</li>
        <li>Content in the public domain</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Generated Content License</h2>
      <p>All podcast episodes generated by Strollcast are released under the <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0)</a>.</p>
      <p>This means you are free to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Share</strong> — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format</li>
        <li><strong>Adapt</strong> — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose, even commercially</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Under the following terms:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Attribution</strong> — You must give appropriate credit to Strollcast and the original paper authors</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>The original research papers remain the intellectual property of their respective authors and publishers. Strollcast creates derivative audio works for educational purposes under fair use principles.</p>
      <p>If you are a copyright holder and believe your work has been used inappropriately, please contact us for prompt removal.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. AI-Generated Content Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>All podcast content is generated using artificial intelligence. While we strive for accuracy:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The AI may occasionally misinterpret or simplify technical content</li>
        <li>Generated podcasts should not be considered a substitute for reading the original paper</li>
        <li>We recommend verifying critical information against the source material</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>Strollcast is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We are not liable for any damages arising from your use of the service.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about these terms or to report copyright concerns, please open an issue on our <a href="https://github.com/strollcast/strollcast" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .terms-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
</style>
